The paper discusses the optimization of wireless networks and proposes a novel infrastructure for the future 5th Generation mobile network infrastructure. It includes technologies such as Massive MIMO systems, Network Functions Virtualization (NFV), Software-Defined Networking (SDN), and Virtual Antenna Arrays (VAA). These topics are related to the fields of Networking and Information Theory (cs.NI, cs.IT), as well as Systems and Control (cs.SY), Distributed Computing (cs.DC), and Architecture (cs.AR).
